$ SSMS Menu: Tools -> Options -> Query Execution -> SQL Server -> Advanced

*Tools -> Options -> Query Execution -> SQL Server -> Advanced* allows to specify «advanced» execution settings:

`SET`
  • `NOCOUNT`
  • `NOEXEC`
  • `PARSEONLY`
  • `CONCAT_NULL_YIELS_NULL`
  • `XACT_ABORT ON`
  • `ARITHABORT`
  • `SHOWPLAN_TEXT`
  • `STATISTICS TIME`
  • `STATISTICS IO`


`SET TRANSACTION ISOLATION LEVEL`:
   • `READ COMMITTED`
   • `READ UNCOMMITTED`
   • `REPEATABLE READ`
   • `SERIALIZABLE`

`SET DEADLOCK PRIORITY`
  • Normal
  • Low

`SET LOCK TIMEOUT`:

`SET QUERY_COVERNOR_COST_LIMIT`

Other settings:
  • Suppress provider message headers
  • Disconnect after the query executes
  • Suppress error messages from unsupported settings


